<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1184,2037]" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1323867422" collectionCode="DZUP" country="Iceland" location="Alto Alegre" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Roraima">
<taxonomicName box="[199,389,1293,1316]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eupteryx">
<emphasis box="[199,389,1293,1316]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">Mesene eupteryx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, originally described as a species, was placed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Stichel" box="[962,1123,1292,1317]" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" refString="Stichel, H. (1923) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Riodinidenfauna Sudamerikas. IV. Nord - Brasilien (Grao - Para). Zeitschrift fur wissenschaftliche Insektenbiologie, 18, 268 - 283." type="journal article" year="1923">Stichel (1923)</bibRefCitation>
as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="Herrich-Schaffer" authorityName="Herrich-Schaffer" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nola">
<emphasis box="[1347,1436,1292,1317]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">M. nola</emphasis>
Herrich-Schäffer
</taxonomicName>
, [1853] (
<figureCitation box="[445,577,1328,1353]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 32" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1766,1789]" captionTargetBox="[232,1349,195,1728]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[232,1350,195,1734]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 32. Mesene species from Parque Nacional da Serra do Divisor, Acre, Brazil (unless otherwise indicated), in dorsal and ventral views. 1 – 2 M. gracielae sp. nov., male holotype. 3 – 4 M. monostigma monostigma, male from Santa Rosa do Purus, Acre, Brazil. 5 – 8 M. nepticula stigmosa, 5 – 6 male; 7 – 8 female. 9 – 12 M. eupteryx stat. rest., 9 – 10 male from Senador Guiomard, Acre, Brazil; 11 – 12 female. 13 – 14 M. nola, male from Alto Alegre, Roraima, Brazil. 15 – 20 M. paraena, 15 – 16 male from Cáceres, Mato Grosso, Brazil; 17 – 18 male; 19 – 20 female. 21 – 28 M. epaphus (23 – 28 upper side left, underside right), 21 – 22 M. epaphus pyrrha, male; 23 female from Porto Acre, Acre, Brazil; 24 female from Senador Guiomard, Acre, Brazil; 25 M. epaphus epaphus, male from Belém, Pará, Brazil; 26 M. epaphus pyrrha, male from São Paulo de Olivença, Amazonas, Brazil; 27 – 28, M. epaphus pyrrha, males from Senador Guiomard, Acre, Brazil. 29 – 32 M. leucophrys, 29 – 30 male from Santa Rosa do Purus, Acre, Brazil; 31 – 32 female. Scale bar 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256291/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">Figs 13–14</figureCitation>
). Specimens deposited at the 
<collectionCode box="[915,988,1329,1352]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/5xp9-edpx" name="Universidade Federal do Parana, Colecao de Entomologia Pe. Jesus Santiago Moure" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">DZUP</collectionCode>
revealed these two taxa in sympatry in 
<collectingCountry box="[151,195,1364,1389]" name="Iceland" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">Ilha</collectingCountry>
de Maracá, 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:BC0E87DAB564DB786CD7B641FE6BFF35:31786017B564DB796D17B720FE24FB3C" box="[343,483,1364,1389]" country="Iceland" name="Alto Alegre" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" stateProvince="Roraima">Alto Alegre</location>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[498,597,1364,1389]" country="Brazil" name="Roraima" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">Roraima</collectingRegion>
</materialsCitation>
, Brazil. The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[957,1048,1364,1389]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nola">
<emphasis box="[957,1048,1364,1389]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">M. nola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1067,1152,1364,1389]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 40" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1900,1923]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,193,1879]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1880]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 40. Male genitalia of Mesene species from Parque Nacional da Serra do Divisor, Acre, Brazil (unless otherwise indicated), in lateral view. 33 M. gracielae sp. nov., holotype. 34 M. monostigma monostigma. 35 M. nepticula stigmosa. 36 M. eupteryx stat. rest. from Senador Guiomard, Acre, Brazil (DZ 36.494). 37 M. nola from Alto Alegre, Roraima, Brazil (DZ 36.794). 38 M. paraena. 39 M. epaphus pyrrha. 40 M. leucophrys. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/161477/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
) differs from that of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eupteryx">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">M. eupteryx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[264,346,1400,1425]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 40" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1900,1923]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,193,1879]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1880]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 40. Male genitalia of Mesene species from Parque Nacional da Serra do Divisor, Acre, Brazil (unless otherwise indicated), in lateral view. 33 M. gracielae sp. nov., holotype. 34 M. monostigma monostigma. 35 M. nepticula stigmosa. 36 M. eupteryx stat. rest. from Senador Guiomard, Acre, Brazil (DZ 36.494). 37 M. nola from Alto Alegre, Roraima, Brazil (DZ 36.794). 38 M. paraena. 39 M. epaphus pyrrha. 40 M. leucophrys. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/161477/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
) by the shorter proximal area of the valva, by the valva distally pointed instead of rounded, and the absence of a short and narrow projection in the inner surface of the valva. Based on these differences we recognize 
<taxonomicName box="[267,400,1473,1496]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eupteryx">
<emphasis box="[267,400,1473,1496]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">M. eupteryx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[407,516,1472,1497]" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">stat. rest.</emphasis>
as a valid species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1184,2037]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1436,151,357]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="470" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1323867420" collectionCode="CAS, DZUP" country="Brazil" county="Disregarding" location="Jauffret" municipality="Amazon" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Para">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,830,1507,1533]" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">
Taxonomic comments 
<collectedFrom box="[465,591,1507,1533]" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">
on 
<taxonomicName box="[501,591,1507,1532]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nola">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[501,591,1507,1532]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">M. nola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</collectedFrom>
and related species.
</emphasis>
The examination of 
<taxonomicName box="[1062,1150,1508,1533]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nola">
<emphasis box="[1062,1150,1508,1533]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">M. nola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other taxa during the taxonomic assessment of 
<taxonomicName box="[436,569,1545,1568]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eupteryx">
<emphasis box="[436,569,1545,1568]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">M. eupteryx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
provided support for some further taxonomic changes. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hall" box="[1189,1436,1544,1569]" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" refString="Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Harvey, D. J. (2002) A survey of androconial organs in the Riodinidae (Lepidoptera). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 136, 171 - 197. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1046 / j. 1096 - 3642.2002.00003. x" type="journal article" year="2002">Hall &amp; Harvey (2002)</bibRefCitation>
cited the additional patch of 
<collectionCode box="[480,534,1581,1605]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15690" name="California Academy of Sciences" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">CAS</collectionCode>
in the tergite 7 observed in 
<taxonomicName authority="White, 1843" authorityName="White" authorityYear="1843" box="[860,1191,1580,1605]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="margaretta">
<emphasis box="[860,1023,1581,1604]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">M. margaretta</emphasis>
(White, 1843)
</taxonomicName>
as unique among the species of 
<taxonomicName box="[275,360,1617,1640]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[275,360,1617,1640]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">Mesene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The study of the abdomen of 
<taxonomicName box="[726,863,1617,1640]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eupteryx">
<emphasis box="[726,863,1617,1640]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">M. eupteryx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[924,1014,1616,1641]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nola">
<emphasis box="[924,1014,1616,1641]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">M. nola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed the presence of the typical 
<taxonomicName box="[151,236,1653,1676]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,236,1653,1676]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">Mesene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distribution of 
<collectionCode box="[411,466,1653,1677]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15690" name="California Academy of Sciences" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">CAS</collectionCode>
in 
<taxonomicName box="[503,636,1653,1676]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eupteryx">
<emphasis box="[503,636,1653,1676]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">M. eupteryx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[654,688,1653,1676]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">i.e.</emphasis>
<collectionCode box="[695,750,1653,1677]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15690" name="California Academy of Sciences" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">CAS</collectionCode>
in tergites 4, 5, and 6), however, an additional patch of 
<collectionCode box="[1382,1436,1653,1677]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15690" name="California Academy of Sciences" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">CAS</collectionCode>
in the tergite 7 was observed in 
<taxonomicName box="[514,602,1688,1713]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nola">
<emphasis box="[514,602,1688,1713]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">M. nola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In additional dissections of specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[1086,1172,1689,1712]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1086,1172,1689,1712]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">Mesene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
available at the 
<collectionCode box="[1359,1432,1689,1712]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/5xp9-edpx" name="Universidade Federal do Parana, Colecao de Entomologia Pe. Jesus Santiago Moure" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">DZUP</collectionCode>
, an additional patch of 
<collectionCode box="[399,453,1725,1749]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15690" name="California Academy of Sciences" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">CAS</collectionCode>
in the tergite 7 was also observed in 
<taxonomicName authority="Hewitson, 1874" authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1874" box="[864,1176,1724,1749]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philonis">
<emphasis box="[864,991,1724,1749]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">M. philonis</emphasis>
Hewitson, 1874
</taxonomicName>
, a species placed in the “ 
<taxonomicName box="[163,252,1760,1785]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phareus">
<emphasis box="[163,252,1760,1785]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">phareus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” species group by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hall" box="[465,714,1760,1785]" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" refString="Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Harvey, D. J. (2002) A survey of androconial organs in the Riodinidae (Lepidoptera). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 136, 171 - 197. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1046 / j. 1096 - 3642.2002.00003. x" type="journal article" year="2002">Hall &amp; Harvey (2002)</bibRefCitation>
. Those authors probably mistook the identity of 
<taxonomicName box="[1253,1380,1760,1785]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philonis">
<emphasis box="[1253,1380,1760,1785]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">M. philonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with an undescribed taxon with similar wing pattern, but with the genitalia and 
<collectionCode box="[996,1050,1797,1821]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15690" name="California Academy of Sciences" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">CAS</collectionCode>
pattern typical of members of the “ 
<taxonomicName box="[163,252,1832,1857]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phareus">
<emphasis box="[163,252,1832,1857]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">phareus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” species group (Dolibaina &amp; Dias, pers. obs.). 
<collectingCounty box="[810,956,1832,1857]" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">Disregarding</collectingCounty>
<taxonomicName box="[967,1098,1832,1857]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philonis">
<emphasis box="[967,1098,1832,1857]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">M. philonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a species widely distributed from the 
<collectingMunicipality box="[254,349,1869,1893]" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">Amazon</collectingMunicipality>
basin to eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[537,608,1868,1893]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:BC0E87DAB564DB786CD7B641FE6BFF35:31786017B564DB796E2CB538FD06F934" box="[620,705,1868,1893]" country="Brazil" county="Disregarding" municipality="Amazon" name="Jauffret" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" stateProvince="Para">Jauffret</location>
&amp; 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:BC0E87DAB564DB786CD7B641FE6BFF35:31786017B564DB796EA5B538FCFDF934" box="[741,826,1868,1893]" country="Brazil" county="Disregarding" municipality="Amazon" name="Jauffret" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" stateProvince="Para">Jauffret</location>
described 
<taxonomicName authority="Jauffret &amp; Jauffret, 2008" authorityName="Jauffret &amp; Jauffret" authorityYear="2008" box="[947,1374,1868,1893]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lecointrei">
<emphasis box="[947,1092,1868,1893]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">M. lecointrei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Jauffret" box="[1098,1374,1868,1893]" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" refString="Jauffret, P. &amp; Jauffret, J. C. (2008) Le genre Mesene Doubleday, 1847 a l'embouchure de l'Amazone. Description d'une nouvelle espece. (Lepidoptera - Riodinidae) (7 eme note). Lambillionea, 108, 309 - 314." type="journal article" year="2008">Jauffret &amp; Jauffret, 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[151,204,1904,1928]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">Pará</collectingRegion>
</materialsCitation>
, 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1323867426" collectionCode="CAS" country="Brazil" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="470" location="In" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" specimenCount="1">
<collectingCountry box="[215,287,1904,1929]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. The distribution, wing pattern and morphology of the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[1107,1251,1904,1929]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lecointrei">
<emphasis box="[1107,1251,1904,1929]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">M. lecointrei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1308,1436,1904,1929]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philonis">
<emphasis box="[1308,1436,1904,1929]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">M. philonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are identical, and therefore we recognize 
<taxonomicName box="[622,766,1940,1965]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lecointrei">
<emphasis box="[622,766,1940,1965]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">M. lecointrei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[1168,1297,1940,1965]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philonis">
<emphasis box="[1168,1297,1940,1965]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">M. philonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1315,1420,1940,1965]" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">syn. nov.</emphasis>
). Nevertheless, 
<bibRefCitation author="Jauffret" box="[310,599,1976,2001]" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" refString="Jauffret, P. &amp; Jauffret, J. C. (2008) Le genre Mesene Doubleday, 1847 a l'embouchure de l'Amazone. Description d'une nouvelle espece. (Lepidoptera - Riodinidae) (7 eme note). Lambillionea, 108, 309 - 314." type="journal article" year="2008">Jauffret &amp; Jauffret (2008)</bibRefCitation>
recognized the similarity between the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[1234,1378,1976,2001]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lecointrei">
<emphasis box="[1234,1378,1976,2001]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">M. lecointrei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[1395,1429,1977,2000]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">i.e.</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[151,282,2012,2037]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philonis">
<emphasis box="[151,282,2012,2037]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">M. philonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName box="[354,445,2012,2037]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nola">
<emphasis box="[354,445,2012,2037]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="469">M. nola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, suggesting a close relationship between those species. The morphology of the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[284,446,153,176]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="470" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="margaretta">
<emphasis box="[284,446,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="470">M. margaretta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hall" box="[460,757,151,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="470" refString="Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Lamas, G. (2007) Four new symmachiine taxa from the eastern Andes of Peru and Ecuador (Lepidoptera: Riodinidae). Zootaxa, 1533, 41 - 52." type="journal article" year="2007">Hall &amp; Lamas 2007, fig. 7</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[779,866,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="470" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nola">
<emphasis box="[779,866,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="470">M. nola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[881,962,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 40" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1900,1923]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,193,1879]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1880]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 40. Male genitalia of Mesene species from Parque Nacional da Serra do Divisor, Acre, Brazil (unless otherwise indicated), in lateral view. 33 M. gracielae sp. nov., holotype. 34 M. monostigma monostigma. 35 M. nepticula stigmosa. 36 M. eupteryx stat. rest. from Senador Guiomard, Acre, Brazil (DZ 36.494). 37 M. nola from Alto Alegre, Roraima, Brazil (DZ 36.794). 38 M. paraena. 39 M. epaphus pyrrha. 40 M. leucophrys. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/161477/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="470">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
) and 
<emphasis box="[1025,1159,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="470">
<taxonomicName box="[1025,1155,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="470" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philonis">M. philonis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
with an entire triangular valva, distally narrow, long and pointed, with a slightly upturned tip, projecting over the aedeagus; the presence of two groups of robust spine-like cornuti, one of which divided in two subgroups, with a small patch of tiny spines in the middle; and the presence of an additional patch of 
<collectionCode box="[790,844,260,284]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15690" name="California Academy of Sciences" pageId="7" pageNumber="470">CAS</collectionCode>
in tergite 7 indicates that these species are closely related, belonging in the same species group. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:BC0E87DAB564DB786CD7B641FE6BFF35:31786017B565DB786EE0B35CFD70FF6E" box="[672,695,296,319]" country="Brazil" name="In" pageId="7" pageNumber="470">In</location>
contrast, further studies are necessary to access the phylogenetic affinities of 
<taxonomicName box="[287,420,333,356]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="470" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eupteryx">
<emphasis box="[287,420,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="470">M. eupteryx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
